'''James Marshall Hackett''' (June 28, 1983 - May 13, 2024) was an American landscaper, camp counselor and serial killer. He had developed a lust for blood in his youth when he killed a bully at the age of six. In his teen hood, he served as a camp counsellor as a means of living out a camp-styled horror movie life. Hackett's official victim count is six, but speculation suggests that it is higher. 

==Life background==
Born in rural North Kill, Upstate New York, James grew up surrounded by nature. His mother, Heather Hackett (born 1960) is a retired police officer from the North Kill Police Department, and his father, Marshall Hackett (1948 - 2008) was a travel agent who claimed to be a Vietnam veteran, but there are no official records of his service. The family had a pet Labrador, Lefty (d. 1992). Marshall and Heather divorced in 1995. Heather married school admin Francis "Frank" Grace (1955 - 2004) in 1997, and Marshall married grocer Robin Justice (born 1978) in 1998. James had three siblings and two nephews: 
* Lynn (biological sister; born 1986) - Wedding planner for The Gomez Company 
** Tucker Morris (born 2015) - Elementary school student 
** Anthony Morris (born 2019) - Elementary school student 
* Amani (biological brother; 1991 - 2011) - University student and self-proclaimed social media "master" content creator 
* Hillary Grace (half-sister; born 1999) - Receptionist for Mountain Energy 
Frank died in 2004 after being mauled by a doberman pincher, around the same time that Marshall and Robin divorced. Amani was killed during his sophomore year of college in a performance of the Running of the Bulls in Spain, where he was attending a class trip. He vlogged the experience on YouTube, where it went semi-viral. 

From an early age, Hackett wanted to work in a career where he would continue to be connected with mother nature. He played baseball in middle school and was also a member of the photography and recycling clubs. He joined the swim team in high school, as well as the fishing and art clubs. Hackett later quit the art club so he could have more time to take on a summer job as a camp counselor at Hackett's Quarry, where he began working at the age of 16. He graduated from high school in 2001. 

After spending the summer of 2001 at Hackett's Quarry and witnessing the 9/11 attacks, James initially expressed interest to enlist in the military to contribute to the War on Terror, but his mother discouraged him from joining. After a brief stint as a male stripper, Hackett got a job as a fisherman, which he worked for a year. Between 2002 and 2003, he worked as a male stripper again. At long last, in 2003, Hackett found work as a landscaper, his dream job, accepting an apprenticeship from The Affleck Company. Subsequently, he resigned from his job as a camp counselor. Hackett's apprenticeship lasted for two years until he received his promotion to the official title in 2005. Over the course of seventeen years, he worked at Affleck and three other companies, including Nashton & Sons from 2011 to 2014, Stone of North Kill from 2016 to 2018, and briefly for Genovese Media in 2020, between his last prison escape and last re-capture. 

Despite expressing his desires to start his own family, Hackett never married or had any of his own children. Regardless, he was a loving and caring uncle to his nephews. 

